msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: A section (5 gatherings) from the middle of a choir psalter containing a number of psalms (part of 67 and all of 71, 74-75, 80, 83-86, 88, 90-91, 94-98, and 102-103) in order for liturgical use, followed by the first half of the hymn Te Deum with square notation in black on 5-line staves in red. Some water damage at the top of most leaves and some repairs, with replaced text in another hand, at the bottom of leaves.

collation.p: Parchment, 40; 1¹ 2-4⁸ 5⁸(-8); modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Psalms written in 15 long lines; Te Deum written in 5 lines with musical notation; psalm texts originally ruled in lead, ornamental double bounding lines and ruling in red ink added after the text was written.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a rounded Gothic script.

binding.p: Gatherings stitched to 6 bands but without binding; some of the penwork was trimmed for binding.

origin.p: Written in Spain in the 16th century.

history.provenance: Sold at auction at Sotheby's, 5 December 1978, lot 59, to Lawrence J. Schoenberg; LJS 291 in the Schoenberg collection.
Gift of Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2009.
